Three types of Variables :
    1. Instance Variables
    2. Static Variables
    3. Local Variables
There are three types of Methods allow in Class
    1. Instance Methods
    2. Static Methods
    3. Local Methods

    constructor



# Default Constructor or ZERO Argument Constructor
# This optional Constructor. Means
    # 1. If developer not interested to decleare , Compiler will automatically create it
     def __init__(self): # Constructor
        self.name='simplilearn'
        self.salery=50
        self.id=101

# This is Called Parametrized Constructor
     def __init__(self,name,id,address): # Constructor
        self.name=name
        self.id = id
        self.address = address
